I will say this, that there never was a redistribution plan presented in this parliament, or in any provincial par- liament in this country, that could be so absolutely justiﬁed as that Alberta redis- tribution was justiﬁed by the Minister of the Interior. However, there was a very material diﬁerence in the cases of Alberta and Saskatchewan. In the case of Alberta ten seats had to be added to ﬁfteen, and it was necessary to very largely recast the lines of the old districts as they had existed for the purposes of representation in the legislature.
